<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Regulation lims:pit-date="2018-01-01" hasPreviousVersion="true" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-01-01" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843130" lims:id="843130" gazette-part="II" regulation-type="SOR" xml:lang="en" in-force="yes" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843131" lims:id="843131"><InstrumentNumber>SOR/2017-40</InstrumentNumber><RegistrationDate><Date><YYYY>2017</YYYY><MM>3</MM><DD>24</DD></Date></RegistrationDate><ConsolidationDate lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></ConsolidationDate><EnablingAuthority lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843133" lims:id="843133"><XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-46">CRIMINAL CODE</XRefExternal></EnablingAuthority><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843134" lims:id="843134">Order Designating New Brunswick for the Purposes of the Criminal Interest Rate Provisions of the Criminal Code</LongTitle><RegulationMakerOrder><RegulationMaker>P.C.</RegulationMaker><OrderNumber>2017-251</OrderNumber><Date><YYYY>2017</YYYY><MM>3</MM><DD>24</DD></Date></RegulationMakerOrder></Identification><Order lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843135" lims:id="843135"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843136" lims:id="843136" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Whereas New Brunswick has legislative measures that protect recipients of payday loans and that provide for limits on the total cost of borrowing under a payday loan agreement;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843137" lims:id="843137" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>And whereas the Lieutenant Governor in Council of New Brunswick has requested that the Governor in Council designate that province for the purposes of section 347.1<FootnoteRef idref="fn_610628-e_hq_3365">a</FootnoteRef> of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-46">Criminal Code</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_610628-e_hq_3366">b</FootnoteRef>;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843138" lims:id="843138" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Therefore, His Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Justice and the Minister of Industry, pursuant to subsection 347.1(3)<FootnoteRef idref="fn_610628-e_hq_3365">a</FootnoteRef> of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-46">Criminal Code</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_610628-e_hq_3366">b</FootnoteRef>, makes the annexed <XRefExternal reference-type="regulation" link="SOR-2017-40">Order Designating New Brunswick for the Purposes of the Criminal Interest Rate Provisions of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-46">Criminal Code</XRefExternal></XRefExternal>.</Text><Footnote id="fn_610628-e_hq_3365" placement="page" status="official"><Label>a</Label><Text>S.C. 2007, c. 9, s. 2</Text></Footnote><Footnote id="fn_610628-e_hq_3366" placement="page" status="official"><Label>b</Label><Text>R.S., c. C-46</Text></Footnote></Provision></Order><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843139" lims:id="843139"><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843140" lims:id="843140" level="1"><TitleText>Province Designated</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-01-01" lims:fid="843141" lims:id="843141"><Label>1</Label><Text>New Brunswick is designated for the purposes of section 347.1 of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="C-46">Criminal Code</XRefExternal>.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2017-03-24" lims:fid="843142" lims:id="843142" level="1"><TitleText>Coming into Force</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-01-01" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-01-01" lims:fid="843143" lims:id="843143"><Label><FootnoteRef idref="fn_Ind7E94_hq_19927">*</FootnoteRef>2</Label><Text>This Order comes into force at 12:00 a.m. Atlantic time on the first day on which the following are both in force:</Text><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2018-01-01" lims:fid="843144" lims:id="843144"><Label>(a)</Label><Text><XRefExternal reference-type="act">An Act Respecting Payday Loans</XRefExternal>, S.N.B. 2008, c. 3; and</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph lims:inforce-start-date="2018-01-01" lims:fid="843145" lims:id="843145"><Label>(b)</Label><Text><XRefExternal reference-type="regulation">Payday Lending Regulation – <XRefExternal reference-type="act">Cost of Credit Disclosure and Payday Loans Act</XRefExternal></XRefExternal>.</Text></Paragraph><Footnote id="fn_Ind7E94_hq_19927" placement="section" status="editorial"><Label>*</Label><Text>[Note: Order in force January 1, 2018.]</Text></Footnote></Section></Body></Regulation>